President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring April 5, 2020, as "Education and Sharing Day, U.S.A." In the proclamation, President Trump emphasizes the importance of education in cultivating curiosity, learning, character development, and collaboration. He pays tribute to Rabbi Menachem Mendel Schneerson, the Lubavitcher Rebbe, for his compassionate leadership and commitment to education. The proclamation highlights Rabbi Schneerson's belief in the potential of all people and the importance of moral and ethical values in education. President Trump calls upon government officials, educators, volunteers, and the people of the United States to observe this day with appropriate programs, ceremonies, and activities.